description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a change in your career? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you ever thought about working within a prison environment, helping to rehabilitate and support offenders to live decent and purposeful lives as a member of the community? Are you looking for a challenging and rewarding role with career developments? Prisons are one of the most challenging, yet rewarding places for healthcare professionals to work - if you’re looking for a role where you can develop your existing skills and learn something new every day, then this is the place to be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for someone wanting a part time Occupational Therapist post working with offenders. There are two part time positions in the Sussex Prisons available (HMP Ford &amp; HMP Lewes) and can be joined to make one full time post if the candidate would like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a Social Care Occupational Therapist position working in partnership with West Sussex County Council, healthcare and prison staff for 15 hours/2 days per week providing assessments, advice, guidance, referrals, equipment requests and housing reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lewes OT will be working with the healthcare teams and liaising with prison staff for referrals into East Sussex County Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary and Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range is £38,000 per annum - dependent on experience (pro-rata if part time).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practice Plus Group benefits include training &amp; development opportunities, company contributory pension scheme, 25 days annual leave plus 8 public bank holidays, staff well-being, access to bank hours, CPD, re-validation, cycle to work scheme, on-site gym facilities and free onsite parking at some locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also proud to support our employees with continued professional development opportunities and further education subject to service needs...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that offers of employment are subject to Practice Plus Group Terms &amp; Conditions and employment is subject to receipt of satisfactory references, enhanced DBS check and prison vetting.&lt;/p&gt;
